{"key":"post-16025975","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>16025975</id>\n<content>You want to use the largest terrarium possible, within reason.&amp;nbsp; A major pinning trigger is fresh air exchange because it reduces the CO2 level.&amp;nbsp; A small terrarium will saturate with CO2 much faster than a larger one where the gasses can dissipate into the air easier.&amp;nbsp; &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;In addition, a larger terrarium has more surface area for the perlite, thus it's &lt;i&gt;easier&lt;/i&gt; to hold humidity, not harder.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>16025981</next>\n<prev>16025958</prev>\n<first>16025855</first>\n<last>16026015</last>\n<when>1333245654</when>\n<utime>04/01/12 05:00 AM</utime>\n</post>"}